      <div class="radio-episode-num">454:</div>
      <h2>Mr. Daisey and the Apple Factory</h2>
      <div class="radio-date">Originally aired <span class="date-display-single">01.06.2012</span></div>
    </div><!--/radio-header-->
    <div class="radio-inner clear-block">
      <div class="thumb">
        <img  class="imagefield imagefield-field_photo_large" width="240" height="180" alt="" src="http://www.thisamericanlife.org/sites/default/files/episodes/454_lg.jpg?1325292433" />              </div>
      <div class="radio-content-wrapper">
        <div class="radio-content">
          Mike Daisey was a self-described "worshipper in the cult of Mac." Then he saw some photos from a new iPhone, taken by workers at the factory where it was made. Mike wondered: Who makes all my crap? He traveled to China to find out.        </div><!--/radio-content-->
